                         : ((value = stringify(value, task.toJSON)),\n                                emitModelChunk(request, task.id, value));\n}\nfunction erroredTask(request, task, error) {\n retryTask(request, task) {\n  if (0 === task.status) {\n    task.status = 5;\n    try {\n      modelRoot = task.model;\n      var resolvedModel = renderModelDestructive(\n        request,\n a Node.js IncomingHttpHeaders object to a Headers object. Any\n * headers with multiple values will be joined with a comma and space. Any\n * headers that have an undefined value will be ignored and others will be\n * coerced to strings.\n *\n * @param nodeHeaders the headers object to convert\n * @returns the converted headers object\n */ export function fromNodeOutgoingHttpHeaders(nodeHeaders) {\n    const headers = new Headers();\n    for (let [key, value] of Object.entries(nodeHeaders)){\n        const values = Array.isArray(value) ? value : [\n            value\n        ];\n        for (let v of values){\n            if (typeof v === 'undefined') continue;\n            if (typeof v === 'number') {\n                v = v.toString();\n            }\n            headers.append(key, v);\n        }\n    }\n    return headers;\n}\n/*\n  Set-Cookie header field-values are sometimes comma joined in one string. This splits them without choking on commas\n  that are within a single set-cookie field-value, such as in the Expires portion.\n  This is uncommon, but explicitly allowed - see https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc2616#section-4.2\n  Node.js does this for every header *except* set-cookie - see https://github.com/nodejs/node/blob/d5e363b77ebaf1caf67cd7528224b651c86815c1/lib/_http_incoming.js#L128\n  React Native's fetch does this for *every* header, including set-cookie.\n  \n  Based on: https://github.com/google/j2objc/commit/16820fdbc8f76ca0c33472810ce0cb03d20efe25\n  Credits to: https://github.com/tomball for original and https://github.com/chrusart for JavaScript implementation\n*/ export function splitCookiesString(cookiesString) {\n    var cookiesStrings = [];\n    var pos = 0;\n    var start;\n    var ch;\n    var lastComma;\n    var nextStart;\n    var cookiesSeparatorFound;\n    function skipWhitespace() {\n        while(pos < cookiesString.length && /\\s/.test(cookiesString.charAt(pos))){\n            pos += 1;\n        }\n        return pos < cookiesString.length;\n    }\n    function notSpecialChar() {\n        ch = cookiesString.charAt(pos);\n        return ch !== '=' && ch !== ';' && ch !== ',';\n    }\n    while(pos < cookiesString.length){\n        start = pos;\n        cookiesSeparatorFound = false;\n        while(skipWhitespace()){\n            ch = cookiesString.charAt(pos);\n            if (ch === ',') {\n                // ',' is a cookie separator if we have later first '=', not ';' or ','\n                lastComma = pos;\n                pos += 1;\n                skipWhitespace();\n                nextStart = pos;\n                while(pos < cookiesString.length && notSpecialChar()){\n                    pos += 1;\n                }\n                // currently special character\n                if (pos < cookiesString.length && cookiesString.charAt(pos) === '=') {\n                    // we found cookies separator\n                    cookiesSeparatorFound = true;\n                    // pos is inside the next cookie, so back up and return it.\n                    pos = nextStart;\n                    cookiesStrings.push(cookiesString.substring(start, lastComma));\n                    start = pos;\n                } else {\n                    // in param ',' or param separator ';',\n                    // we continue from that comma\n                    pos = lastComma + 1;\n                }\n            } else {\n                pos += 1;\n            }\n        }\n        if (!cookiesSeparatorFound || pos >= cookiesString.length) {\n            cookiesStrings.push(cookiesString.substring(start, cookiesString.length));\n        }\n    }\n    return cookiesStrings;\n}\n/**\n * Converts a Headers object to a Node.js OutgoingHttpHeaders object. This is\n * required to support the set-cookie header, which may have multiple values.\n *\n * @param headers the headers object to convert\n * @returns the converted headers object\n */ export function toNodeOutgoingHttpHeaders(headers) {\n    const nodeHeaders = {};\n    const cookies = [];\n    if (headers) {\n        for (const [key, value] of headers.entries()){\n            if (key.toLowerCase() === 'set-cookie') {\n                // We may have gotten a comma joined string of cookies, or multiple\n                // set-cookie headers. We need to merge them into one header array\n                // to represent all the cookies.\n                cookies.push(...splitCookiesString(value));\n                nodeHeaders[key] = cookies.length === 1 ? cookies[0] : cookies;\n            } else {\n                nodeHeaders[key] = value;\n            }\n        }\n    }\n    return nodeHeaders;\n}\n/**\n * Validate the correctness of a user-provided URL.\n */ export function validateURL(url) {\n    try {\n        return String(new URL(String(url)));\n    } catch (error) {\n        throw Object.defineProperty(new Error(`URL is malformed \"${String(url)}\". The path shouldn't be an API path. If a default locale is given the\n * prefix will be omitted if the locale is already the default locale.\n */\nexport function addLocale(\n  path: string,\n  locale?: string | false,\n  defaultLocale?: string,\n  ignorePrefix?: boolean\n) {\n  // If no locale was given or the locale is the default locale, we don't need\n  // to prefix the path.\n  if (!locale || locale === defaultLocale) return path\n\n  const lower = path.toLowerCase()\n\n  // If the path is an API path or the path already has the locale prefix, we\n  // don't need to prefix the path.\n  if (!ignorePrefix) {\n    if (pathHasPrefix(lower, '/api')) return path\n    if (pathHasPrefix(lower, `/${locale.toLowerCase()}`)) return path\n  }\n\n  // Add the locale prefix to the path.\n  return addPathPrefix(path, `/${locale}`)\n}\n","import type { NextPathnameInfo } from './get-next-pathname-info'\nimport { removeTrailingSlash } from './remove-trailing-slash'\nimport { addPathPrefix } from './add-path-prefix'\nimport { addPathSuffix } from './add-path-suffix'\nimport { addLocale } from './add-locale'\n\ninterface ExtendedInfo extends NextPathnameInfo {\n  defaultLocale?: string\n  ignorePrefix?: boolean\n}\n\nexport function formatNextPathnameInfo(info: ExtendedInfo) {\n  let pathname = addLocale(\n    info.pathname,\n    info.locale,\n    info.buildId ? undefined : info.defaultLocale,\n    info.ignorePrefix\n  )\n\n  if (info.buildId || !info.trailingSlash) {\n    pathname = removeTrailingSlash(pathname)\n  }\n\n  if (info.buildId) {\n    pathname = addPathSuffix(\n      addPathPrefix(pathname, `/_next/data/${info.buildId}`),\n      info.pathname === '/' ? This is stored as a\n * WeakMap so if the locales are garbage collected, the cache entry will be\n * removed as well.\n */\nconst cache = new WeakMap<readonly string[], readonly string[]>()\n\n/**\n * For a pathname that may include a locale from a list of locales, it\n * removes the locale from the pathname returning it alongside with the\n * detected locale.\n *\n * @param pathname A pathname that may include a locale.\n * @param locales A list of locales.\n * @returns The detected locale and pathname without locale\n */\nexport function normalizeLocalePath(\n  pathname: string,\n  locales?: readonly string[]\n): PathLocale {\n  // If locales is undefined, return the pathname as is.\n  if (!locales) return { pathname }\n\n  // Get the cached lowercased locales or create a new cache entry.\n  let lowercasedLocales = cache.get(locales)\n  if (!lowercasedLocales) {\n    lowercasedLocales = locales.map((locale) => locale.toLowerCase())\n    cache.set(locales, lowercasedLocales)\n  }\n\n  let detectedLocale: string | undefined\n\n  // The first segment will be empty, because it has a leading `/`. If\n  // there is no further segment, there is no locale (or it's the default).\n  const segments = pathname.split('/', 2)\n\n  // If there's no second segment (ie, the pathname is just `/`), there's no\n  // locale.\n  if (!segments[1]) return { pathname }\n\n  // The second segment will contain the locale part if any.\n  const segment = segments[1].toLowerCase()\n\n  // See if the segment matches one of the locales. If it doesn't, there is\n  // no locale (or it's the default).\n  const index = lowercasedLocales.indexOf(segment)\n  if (index < 0) return { pathname }\n\n  // Return the case-sensitive locale.\n  detectedLocale = locales[index]\n\n  // Remove the `/${locale}` part of the pathname.\n  pathname = pathname.slice(detectedLocale.length + 1) || '/'\n\n  return { pathname, detectedLocale }\n}\n","import { pathHasPrefix } from './path-has-prefix'\n\n/**\n * Given a path and a prefix it will remove the prefix when it exists in the\n * given path. It ensures it matches exactly without containing extra chars\n * and if the prefix is not there it will be noop.\n *\n * @param path The path to remove the prefix from.\n * @param prefix The prefix to be removed.\n */\nexport function removePathPrefix(path: string, prefix: string): string {\n  // If the path doesn't start with the prefix we can return it as is. This\n  // protects us from situations where the prefix is a substring of the path\n  // prefix such as:\n  //\n  // For prefix: /blog\n  //\n  //   /blog -> true\n  //   /blog/ -> true\n  //   /blog/1 -> true\n  //   /blogging -> false\n  //   /blogging/ -> false\n  //   /blogging/1 -> false\n  if (!pathHasPrefix(path, prefix)) {\n    return path\n  }\n\n  // Remove the prefix from the path via slicing.\n  const withoutPrefix = path.slice(prefix.length)\n\n  // If the path without the prefix starts with a `/` we can return it as is.\n  if (withoutPrefix.startsWith('/')) {\n    return withoutPrefix\n  }\n\n  // If the path without the prefix doesn't start with a `/` we need to add it\n  // back to the path to make sure it's a valid path.\n  return `/${withoutPrefix}`\n}\n","import { normalizeLocalePath } from '../../i18n/normalize-locale-path'\nimport { removePathPrefix } from './remove-path-prefix'\nimport { pathHasPrefix } from './path-has-prefix'\nimport type { I18NProvider } from '../../../../server/lib/i18n-provider'\n\nexport interface NextPathnameInfo {\n  /**\n   * The base path in case the pathname included it.\n   */\n  basePath?: string\n  /**\n   * The buildId for when the parsed URL is a data URL. This assumes that there is\n                // no mixed case keys (e.g. \"Content-Type\" and \"content-type\") in the\n                // headers object.\n                const original = Object.keys(headers).find((o)=>o.toLowerCase() === lowercased);\n                // If the original casing doesn't exist, return undefined.\n                if (typeof original === 'undefined') return;\n                // If the original casing exists, return the value.\n                return ReflectAdapter.get(target, original, receiver);\n            },\n            set (target, prop, value, receiver) {\n                if (typeof prop === 'symbol') {\n                    return ReflectAdapter.set(target, prop, value, receiver);\n                }\n                const lowercased = prop.toLowerCase();\n                // Let's find the original casing of the key. HeadersAdapter(headers);\n    }\n    append(name, value) {\n        const existing = this.headers[name];\n        if (typeof existing === 'string') {\n            this.headers[name] = [\n                existing,\n                value\n            ];\n        } else if (Array.isArray(existing)) {\n            existing.push(value);\n        } else {\n            this.headers[name] = value;\n     writable: true\n    };\n    Object.defineProperty(req, prop, {\n        ...opts,\n        get: ()=>{\n            const value = getter();\n            // we set the property on the object to avoid       this.totalSize -= this.sizes.get(key) || 0;\n        }\n        this.cache.set(key, value);\n        this.sizes.set(key, size);\n        this.totalSize += size;\n        this.touch(key);\n this.cache.get(key);\n        if (value === undefined) {\n            return undefined;\n        }\n        this.touch(key);\n        return value;\n    }\n    touch(key) {\n        const value = sourceMappingURL=after-context.js.map","/**\n * Calls the given async function only when the returned promise-like object is\n * awaited. Afterwards, it provides the resolved value synchronously as `value`\n * property.\n */ export function createLazyResult(fn) {\n    let pendingResult;\n    const result = {\n        then (onfulfilled, onrejected) {\n            if (!pendingResult) {\n                pendingResult = fn();\n            }\n            pendingResult.then((value)=>{\n                result.value = value;\n            }).catch(()=>{\n            // The externally awaited result will be rejected via `onrejected`. This is primarily\n * useful for dynamicIO where we use promise resolution timing to determine which\n * parts of a render can be included in a prerender.\n *\n * @internal\n */ export function makeHangingPromise(signal, expression) {\n    if (signal.aborted) {\n        return Promise.reject(new HangingPromiseRejectionError(expression));\n    } else {\n        const hangingPromise = new Promise((_, reject)=>{\n            const boundRejection = reject.bind(null, new HangingPromiseRejectionError(expression));\n            let currentListeners = abortListenersBySignal.get(signal);\n            if (currentListeners) {\n                currentListeners.push(boundRejection);\n            } else {\n                const listeners = [\n                    boundRejection\n                ];\n                abortListenersBySignal.set(signal, listeners);\n                signal.addEventListener('abort', ()=>{\n                    for(let i = 0; i < listeners.length; i++){\n                        listeners[i]();\n                    }\n                }, {\n                    once: true\n                });\n            }\n        });\n        // We are fine if no one actually awaits this promise. If you actually await somewhere or construct\n        // your own promise out of it you'll need to ensure you handle the error when it rejects.\n        hangingPromise.catch(ignoreReject);\n        return hangingPromise;\n    }\n}\nfunction ignoreReject() {}\n\n//# sourceMappingURL=dynamic-rendering-utils.js.map","export const METADATA_BOUNDARY_NAME = '__next_metadata_boundary__';\nexport const VIEWPORT_BOUNDARY_NAME = '__next_viewport_boundary__';\nexport const OUTLET_BOUNDARY_NAME = '__next_outlet_boundary__';\n\n//# sourceMappingURL=metadata-constants.js.map","/**\n * The functions provided by this module are used to communicate certain properties\n * about the currently running code so that Next.js can make decisions on how to handle\n * the current execution in different rendering modes such as pre-rendering, resuming, and SSR.\n *\n * Today Next.js treats all code as potentially static. Certain APIs may only make sense when dynamically rendering.\n * Traditionally this meant deopting the entire render to dynamic however with PPR we can now deopt parts\n * of a React tree as dynamic while still keeping other parts static. There are really two different kinds of\n * Dynamic indications.\n *\n * The first is simply an intention to be dynamic. unstable_noStore is an example of this where\n * the currently executing code simply declares that the current scope is dynamic but if you use it\n * inside unstable_cache it can still be cached. This type of indication can be removed if we ever\n * make the default dynamic to begin with because the only way you would ever be static is inside\n * a cache scope which this indication does not affect.\n *\n * The second is an indication that a dynamic data source was read. This is a stronger form of dynamic\n * because it means that it is inappropriate to cache this at all. using a dynamic data source inside\n * unstable_cache should error. If the input\n        // we're waiting on is coming from another cache, we do want to wait for it so that\n        // we can resolve this cache entry too.\n        workUnitStore.cacheSignal.inputReady().then(()=>{\n            controller.abort();\n        });\n    } else {\n        // Otherwise we're in the final render and we should already have all our caches\n        // filled. async function middleware(request: NextRequest) {\n  // Fallback defensivo si el paquete de auth aún no expone constantes\n  const AUTH_COOKIES =\n    AUTH_COOKIES_IMPORTED ??\n    ({ token: It MUST begin with a\n * lowercase letter, and can only contain lowercase letters a-z, digits 0-9,\n * underscores _, dashes -, asterisks *, and forward slashes /.\n * For multi-tenant vendor scenarios, an at sign (@) can be used to prefix the\n * vendor name. Vendors SHOULD set the tenant ID at the beginning of the key.\n * see https://www.w3.org/TR/trace-context/#key\n */\nexport function validateKey(key) {\n    return VALID_KEY_REGEX.test(key);\n}\n/**\n * Value is opaque string up to 256 characters printable ASCII RFC0020\n * characters (i.e., the range 0x20 to 0x7E) except comma , and =.\n */\nexport function validateValue(value) {\n    return (VALID_VALUE_BASE_REGEX.test(value) &&\n        !INVALID_VALUE_COMMA_EQUAL_REGEX.test(value));\n}\n//# sourceMappingURL=tracestate-validators.js.map","/*\n * Copyright The OpenTelemetry Authors\n *\n * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n *\n *      https://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n *\n * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n * limitations under the License.\n */\nimport { validateKey, validateValue } from './tracestate-validators';\nvar MAX_TRACE_STATE_ITEMS = 32;\nvar MAX_TRACE_STATE_LEN = 512;\nvar LIST_MEMBERS_SEPARATOR = ',';\nvar LIST_MEMBER_KEY_VALUE_SPLITTER = '=';\n/**\n * TraceState must be a class and not a simple object type because of the spec\n * requirement (https://www.w3.org/TR/trace-context/#tracestate-field).\n *\n * Here is the list of allowed mutations:\n * - New key-value pair should be added into the beginning of the list\n * - The value of any key can be updated. Modified keys MUST be moved to the\n * beginning of the list.\n */\nvar TraceStateImpl = /** @class */ (function () {\n    function TraceStateImpl(rawTraceState) {\n        this._internalState = new Map();\n        if (rawTraceState)\n            this._parse(rawTraceState);\n    }\n    TraceStateImpl.prototype.set = function (key, value) {\n        // TODO: Benchmark the different approaches(map vs list) and\n        // use the faster one.\n        var traceState = this._clone();\n        if (traceState._internalState.has(key)) {\n            traceState._internalState.delete(key);\n        }\n        traceState._internalState.set(key, value);\n        return traceState;\n    };\n    TraceStateImpl.prototype.unset = function (key) {\n        var traceState = this._clone();\n        traceState._internalState.delete(key);\n        return traceState;\n    };\n    TraceStateImpl.prototype.get = function (key) {\n        return this._internalState.get(key);\n    };\n    TraceStateImpl.prototype.serialize = function () {\n        var _this = this;\n        return this._keys()\n            .reduce(function (agg, key) {\n            agg.push(key + LIST_MEMBER_KEY_VALUE_SPLITTER + _this.get(key));\n            return agg;\n        }, [])\n            .join(LIST_MEMBERS_SEPARATOR);\n    };\n    TraceStateImpl.prototype._parse = function (rawTraceState) {\n        if (rawTraceState.length > MAX_TRACE_STATE_LEN)\n            return;\n        this._internalState = rawTraceState\n            .split(LIST_MEMBERS_SEPARATOR)\n            .reverse() // Store in reverse so new keys (.set(...)) will be placed at the beginning\n            .reduce(function (agg, part) {\n            var listMember = part.trim(); // Optional Whitespace (OWS) handling\n            var i = listMember.indexOf(LIST_MEMBER_KEY_VALUE_SPLITTER);\n            if (i !== -1) {\n                var key = listMember.slice(0, i);\n                var value = listMember.slice(i + 1, part.length);\n                if (validateKey(key) && validateValue(value)) {\n                    agg.set(key, value);\n                }\n                else {\n                    // TODO: Consider to add warning log\n                }\n            }\n            return agg;\n        }, new Map());\n        // Because of the reverse() requirement, trunc must be done after map is created\n        if (this._internalState.size > MAX_TRACE_STATE_ITEMS) {\n            this._internalState = new Map(Array.from(this._internalState.entries())\n                .reverse() // Use reverse same as original tracestate parse chain\n                .slice(0, MAX_TRACE_STATE_ITEMS));\n        }\n    };\n    TraceStateImpl.prototype._keys = function () {\n        return Array.from(this._internalState.keys()).reverse();\n    };\n    TraceStateImpl.prototype._clone = function () {\n        var traceState = new TraceStateImpl();\n        traceState._internalState = new Map(this._internalState);\n        return traceState;\n    };\n    return TraceStateImpl;\n}());\nexport { TraceStateImpl };\n//# sourceMappingURL=tracestate-impl.js.map","/*\n * Copyright The autenticación unificado - Migrado desde auth-service\n */\n\n'use client';\n\nimport { getFirebaseAuth, getFirebaseFirestore } from '@altamedica/firebase';\nimport {\n  Auth,\n  createUserWithEmailAndPassword,\n  User as FirebaseUser,\n  GoogleAuthProvider,\n  onAuthStateChanged,\n  sendEmailVerification,\n  sendPasswordResetEmail,\n  signInWithEmailAndPassword,\n  signInWithPopup,\n  signOut,\n  updateProfile,\n} from 'firebase/auth';\nimport { doc, Firestore, getDoc, serverTimestamp, setDoc, updateDoc } from 'firebase/firestore';\n// Simple logger implementation to avoid circular dependencies\ntype LogData = unknown;\nconst logger = {\n  info: (message: string, data?: LogData) => {\n    if (typeof console !== 'undefined' && process.env.NODE_ENV !== 'production') {\n      console.log(message, data);\n    }\n  },\n  warn: (message: string, data?: LogData) => {\n    if (typeof console !== 'undefined') {\n      console.warn(message, data);\n    }\n  },\n  error: (message: string, data?: LogData) => {\n    if (typeof console !== 'undefined') {\n      console.error(message, data);\n    }\n  },\n  debug: (message: string, data?: LogData) => {\n    if (typeof console !== 'undefined' && process.env.NODE_ENV !== 'production') {\n      console.debug(message, data);\n    }\n  },\n};\n// TODO: Definir UserRole en @altamedica/types\n// Stub temporal para permitir el build\nenum UserRole {\n  PATIENT = 'patient',\n  DOCTOR = 'doctor',\n  COMPANY = 'company',\n  ADMIN = 'admin',\n}\n// Función auxiliar para normalizar roles\nconst normalizeUserRole = (role: string): UserRole => {\n  const key = role?.toString().trim().toLowerCase();\n  switch (key) {\n    case 'admin':\n    case 'ADMIN':\n    case 'platform-admin':\n      return UserRole.ADMIN;\n    case 'doctor':\n    case 'medical_director':\n    case 'nurse':\n      return UserRole.DOCTOR;\n    case 'company':\n    case 'company-admin':\n    case 'company_admin':\n      return UserRole.COMPANY;\n    case 'patient':\n    default:\n      return UserRole.PATIENT;\n  }\n};\n\n// Eliminado enum duplicado: se usan los roles canónicos. Si un flujo requiere \"estado previo a selección\"\n// se utilizará profileComplete=false y/o un campo temporal pendingRole en Firestore.\n\nexport interface User {\n  id: string;\n  uid: string;\n  email: string;\n  displayName: string;\n  role: UserRole; // Rol canónico validado\n  pendingRoleSelection?: boolean; // Si true, frontend debe forzar elección (antes se usaba GUEST)\n  photoURL?: string;\n  emailVerified: boolean;\n  profileComplete?: boolean;\n  /**\n   * Token JWT (idToken de Firebase) expuesto opcionalmente para clientes que necesitan\n   * llamar endpoints backend via fetch con Authorization Bearer. Mantenerlo opcional\n   * para no romper contratos existentes; se rellena dinámicamente al construir User.\n   */\n  token?: string;\n  metadata?: {\n    lastLoginAt?: string;\n    createdAt?: string;\n  };\n  // Campos específicos por rol\n  patientData?: {\n    medicalRecordNumber?: string;\n    dateOfBirth?: string;\n    bloodType?: string;\n  };\n  doctorData?: {\n    licenseNumber?: string;\n    specialties?: string[];\n    hospitalAffiliations?: string[];\n  };\n  companyData?: {\n    companyId?: string;\n    department?: string;\n    position?: string;\n  };\n}\n\nexport interface AuthState {\n  user: User | null;\n  isAuthenticated: boolean;\n  isLoading: boolean;\n  error: string | null;\n}\n\nexport interface LoginCredentials {\n  email: string;\n  password: string;\n}\n\n// Roles disponibles para registro público (sin admin)\nexport enum PublicUserRole {\n  DOCTOR = 'doctor',\n  PATIENT = 'patient',\n  COMPANY = 'company',\n}\n\nexport interface RegisterData extends LoginCredentials {\n  firstName: string;\n  lastName: string;\n  role?: PublicUserRole; // Solo roles públicos permitidos en registro\n  displayName?: string; // Opcional, se genera automáticamente desde firstName + lastName\n}\n\n// Clase principal del servicio\nexport class AuthService {\n  private _auth: Auth | null = null;\n  private _db: Firestore | null = null;\n  private googleProvider: GoogleAuthProvider;\n\n  constructor() {\n    this.googleProvider = new GoogleAuthProvider();\n    // Configurar scopes para obtener información adicional\n    this.googleProvider.addScope('profile');\n    this.googleProvider.addScope('email');\n    // Forzar selección de cuenta\n    this.googleProvider.setCustomParameters({\n      prompt: 'select_account',\n    });\n  }\n\n  private get auth(): Auth {\n    if (!this._auth) {\n      this._auth = getFirebaseAuth();\n    }\n    return this._auth;\n  }\n\n  private get db(): Firestore {\n    if (!this._db) {\n      this._db = getFirebaseFirestore();\n    }\n    return this._db;\n  }\n\n  /**\n   * Registra un nuevo usuario\n   */\n  async signUp(data: RegisterData): Promise<User> {\n    try {\n      // Validar que el rol no sea admin (seguridad adicional)\n      if ((data.role as any) === 'admin') {\n        throw new Error('El rol de administrador no está disponible para registro público');\n      }\n\n      // Validar campos requeridos\n      if (!data.firstName || !data.lastName) {\n        throw new Error('firstName y lastName son campos requeridos');\n      }\n\n      // Crear usuario en Firebase Auth\n      const credential = await createUserWithEmailAndPassword(this.auth, data.email, data.password);\n\n      // Actualizar perfil con nombre completo\n      const displayName = data.displayName || `${data.firstName} ${data.lastName}`;\n      await updateProfile(credential.user, {\n        displayName: displayName,\n      });\n\n      // Enviar email de verificación\n      await sendEmailVerification(credential.user);\n\n      // Crear perfil en Firestore - Solo roles públicos permitidos\n      const userData: User = {\n        id: credential.user.uid,\n        uid: credential.user.uid,\n        email: data.email,\n        displayName: displayName,\n        role: data.role ? (data.role as unknown as UserRole) : UserRole.PATIENT, // Mapeo de roles\n        emailVerified: false,\n        profileComplete: false,\n        metadata: {\n          createdAt: new Date().toISOString(),\n          lastLoginAt: new Date().toISOString(),\n        },\n      };\n\n      await setDoc(doc(this.db, 'users', credential.user.uid), {\n        ...userData,\n        createdAt: serverTimestamp(),\n        updatedAt: serverTimestamp(),\n      });\n\n      return userData;\n    } catch (error: any) {\n      throw this.handleAuthError(error);\n    }\n  }\n\n  /**\n   * Inicia sesión con email y contraseña\n   */\n  async login(credentials: LoginCredentials): Promise<User> {\n    try {\n      const credential = await signInWithEmailAndPassword(\n        this.auth,\n        credentials.email,\n        credentials.password,\n      );\n      // Establecer cookie httpOnly de sesión en backend usando idToken (flujo único)\n      try {\n        const apiBase = process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL || 'http://localhost:3001';\n        const idToken = await credential.user.getIdToken();\n        await fetch(`${apiBase}/api/v1/auth/session-login`, {\n          method: 'POST',\n          headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },\n          credentials: 'include',\n          body: JSON.stringify({ idToken }),\n        });\n      } catch (e) {\n        logger.warn('[AuthService] No se pudo establecer cookie de sesión httpOnly:', e);\n      }\n\n      return await this.getUserData(credential.user);\n    } catch (error: any) {\n      throw this.handleAuthError(error);\n    }\n  }\n\n  /**\n   * Inicia sesión con Google\n   */\n  async loginWithGoogle(): Promise<User> {\n    try {\n      let credential: any;\n      try {\n        credential = await signInWithPopup(this.auth, this.googleProvider);\n      } catch (popupError: any) {\n        const fallbackCodes = new Set([\n          'auth/internal-error',\n          'auth/popup-blocked',\n          'auth/cancelled-popup-request',\n          'auth/popup-closed-by-user',\n        ]);\n        if (fallbackCodes.has(popupError?.code)) {\n          const { signInWithRedirect } = await import('firebase/auth');\n          await signInWithRedirect(this.auth, this.googleProvider);\n          // La app continuará en getRedirectResult al recargar. Lanzamos un error controlado.\n          throw new Error('GOOGLE_SIGNIN_REDIRECT_INITIATED');\n        }\n        throw popupError;\n      }\n\n      // Verificar si es un usuario nuevo\n      const userDoc = await getDoc(doc(this.db, 'users', credential.user.uid));\n\n      if (!userDoc.exists()) {\n        // Crear perfil para nuevo usuario Google con rol mínimo (patient) y bandera de selección pendiente\n        const userData: User = {\n          id: credential.user.uid,\n          uid: credential.user.uid,\n          email: credential.user.email!,\n          displayName: credential.user.displayName || credential.user.email!.split('@')[0],\n          role: UserRole.PATIENT,\n          pendingRoleSelection: true,\n          photoURL: credential.user.photoURL || undefined,\n          emailVerified: credential.user.emailVerified,\n          profileComplete: false,\n          metadata: {\n            createdAt: new Date().toISOString(),\n            lastLoginAt: new Date().toISOString(),\n          },\n        };\n\n        await setDoc(doc(this.db, 'users', credential.user.uid), {\n          ...userData,\n          createdAt: serverTimestamp(),\n          updatedAt: serverTimestamp(),\n        });\n\n        return userData;\n      }\n\n      // Establecer cookie httpOnly de sesión con idToken\n      try {\n        const apiBase = process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL || 'http://localhost:3001';\n        const idToken = await credential.user.getIdToken();\n        await fetch(`${apiBase}/api/v1/auth/session-login`, {\n          method: 'POST',\n          headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },\n          credentials: 'include',\n          body: JSON.stringify({ idToken }),\n        });\n      } catch (e) {\n        logger.warn('[AuthService] No se pudo establecer cookie de sesión httpOnly (Google):', e);\n      }\n\n      return await this.getUserData(credential.user);\n    } catch (error: any) {\n      throw this.handleAuthError(error);\n    }\n  }\n\n  /**\n   * Cierra sesión\n   */\n  async logout(): Promise<void> {\n    try {\n      await signOut(this.auth);\n      // Limpiar cookie de sesión httpOnly en backend\n      try {\n        const apiBase = process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL || 'http://localhost:3001';\n        await fetch(`${apiBase}/api/v1/auth/session-logout`, {\n          method: 'POST',\n          credentials: 'include',\n        });\n      } catch {\n        // Ignore logout errors\n      }\n    } catch (error: any) {\n      throw this.handleAuthError(error);\n    }\n  }\n\n  /**\n   * Registro especial de administrador - Solo para uso interno\n   * @param adminKey Clave especial para crear admins\n   * @param userData Datos del usuario admin\n   */\n  async registerAdmin(\n    adminKey: string,\n    userData: LoginCredentials & { displayName: string },\n  ): Promise<User> {\n    // Clave especial que solo Eduardo conoce\n    const ADMIN_SECRET_KEY = 'altamedica_admin_2025_eduardo_secret';\n\n    if (adminKey !== ADMIN_SECRET_KEY) {\n      throw new Error('No autorizado para crear administradores');\n    }\n\n    try {\n      // Crear usuario en Firebase Auth\n      const credential = await createUserWithEmailAndPassword(\n        this.auth,\n        userData.email,\n        userData.password,\n      );\n\n      const user = credential.user;\n      await updateProfile(user, { displayName: userData.displayName });\n\n      // Crear usuario en Firestore con rol admin\n      const newUser: User = {\n        id: user.uid,\n        uid: user.uid,\n        email: user.email!,\n        displayName: userData.displayName,\n        role: UserRole.ADMIN, // Forzar rol admin\n        emailVerified: user.emailVerified,\n        profileComplete: true,\n        metadata: {\n          createdAt: new Date().toISOString(),\n          lastLoginAt: new Date().toISOString(),\n        },\n      };\n\n      await setDoc(doc(this.db, 'users', user.uid), newUser);\n      logger.info(`[AuthService] ⚡ Usuario ADMIN creado: ${userData.email}`, undefined);\n      return newUser;\n    } catch (error: any) {\n      logger.error('[AuthService] Error creando admin:', error);\n      throw new Error(`Error en registro de administrador: ${error.message}`);\n    }\n  }\n\n  /**\n   * Envía email para resetear contraseña\n   */\n  async resetPassword(email: string): Promise<void> {\n    try {\n      await sendPasswordResetEmail(this.auth, email);\n    } catch (error: any) {\n      throw this.handleAuthError(error);\n    }\n  }\n\n  /**\n   * Obtiene el usuario actual\n   */\n  async getCurrentUser(): Promise<User | null> {\n    const firebaseUser = this.auth.currentUser;\n\n    if (!firebaseUser) {\n      return null;\n    }\n\n    return await this.getUserData(firebaseUser);\n  }\n\n  /**\n   * Actualiza el perfil del usuario\n   */\n  async updateUserProfile(userId: string, updates: Partial<User>): Promise<void> {\n    try {\n      const userRef = doc(this.db, 'users', userId);\n\n      await updateDoc(userRef, {\n        ...updates,\n        updatedAt: serverTimestamp(),\n      });\n\n      // Si hay cambios en displayName o photoURL, actualizar también en Firebase Auth\n      const currentUser = this.auth.currentUser;\n      if (currentUser && currentUser.uid === userId) {\n        const authUpdates: any = {};\n\n        if (updates.displayName) {\n          authUpdates.displayName = updates.displayName;\n        }\n        if (updates.photoURL) {\n          authUpdates.photoURL = updates.photoURL;\n        }\n\n        if (Object.keys(authUpdates).length > 0) {\n          await updateProfile(currentUser, authUpdates);\n        }\n      }\n    } catch (error: any) {\n      throw this.handleAuthError(error);\n    }\n  }\n\n  /**\n   * Verifica si el usuario tiene un rol específico\n   */\n  async hasRole(userId: string, role: UserRole): Promise<boolean> {\n    try {\n      const userDoc = await getDoc(doc(this.db, 'users', userId));\n\n      if (!userDoc.exists()) {\n        return false;\n      }\n\n      const userData = userDoc.data() as User;\n      return userData.role === role;\n    } catch (error) {\n      logger.error('Error checking user role:', error);\n      return false;\n    }\n  }\n\n  /**\n   * Verifica si el usuario tiene alguno de los roles especificados\n   */\n  async hasAnyRole(userId: string, roles: UserRole[]): Promise<boolean> {\n    try {\n      const userDoc = await getDoc(doc(this.db, 'users', userId));\n\n      if (!userDoc.exists()) {\n        return false;\n      }\n\n      const userData = userDoc.data() as User;\n      return roles.includes(userData.role);\n    } catch (error) {\n      logger.error('Error checking user roles:', error);\n      return false;\n    }\n  }\n\n  /**\n   * Suscribe a cambios en el estado de autenticación\n   */\n  onAuthStateChange(callback: (user: User | null) => void): () => void {\n    return onAuthStateChanged(this.auth, async (firebaseUser) => {\n      if (firebaseUser) {\n        const user = await this.getUserData(firebaseUser);\n        callback(user);\n      } else {\n        callback(null);\n      }\n    });\n  }\n\n  /**\n   * Obtiene los datos del usuario desde Firestore\n   */\n  private async getUserData(firebaseUser: FirebaseUser): Promise<User> {\n    try {\n      const userDoc = await getDoc(doc(this.db, 'users', firebaseUser.uid));\n      // Obtener idToken fresco para adjuntarlo al objeto User\n      let idToken: string | undefined;\n      try {\n        idToken = await firebaseUser.getIdToken(/* forceRefresh */ false);\n      } catch (e) {\n        // ignorar fallo de token, continuar sin token\n      }\n\n      if (!userDoc.exists()) {\n        // Si no existe en Firestore, crear perfil mínimo con rol patient + pendingRoleSelection\n        const userData: User = {\n          id: firebaseUser.uid,\n          uid: firebaseUser.uid,\n          email: firebaseUser.email!,\n          displayName: firebaseUser.displayName || firebaseUser.email!.split('@')[0],\n          role: UserRole.PATIENT,\n          pendingRoleSelection: true,\n          photoURL: firebaseUser.photoURL || undefined,\n          emailVerified: firebaseUser.emailVerified,\n          profileComplete: false,\n        };\n\n        await setDoc(doc(this.db, 'users', firebaseUser.uid), {\n          ...userData,\n          createdAt: serverTimestamp(),\n          updatedAt: serverTimestamp(),\n        });\n\n        return userData;\n      }\n\n      // Actualizar última vez que inició sesión\n      await updateDoc(doc(this.db, 'users', firebaseUser.uid), {\n        'metadata.lastLoginAt': new Date().toISOString(),\n        updatedAt: serverTimestamp(),\n      });\n\n      const userData = userDoc.data() as User;\n      // Normalizar rol básico: asegurar que pertenezca al enum, si no fallback\n      if (!Object.values(UserRole).includes(userData.role)) {\n        userData.role = UserRole.PATIENT;\n        userData.pendingRoleSelection = true;\n      }\n\n      // Asegurar que los campos básicos estén sincronizados\n      userData.emailVerified = firebaseUser.emailVerified;\n      userData.email = firebaseUser.email!;\n\n      if (idToken) {\n        userData.token = idToken;\n      }\n      return userData;\n    } catch (error) {\n      logger.error('Error getting user data:', error);\n\n      // Retornar datos básicos si hay error\n      const fallback: User = {\n        id: firebaseUser.uid,\n        uid: firebaseUser.uid,\n        email: firebaseUser.email!,\n        displayName: firebaseUser.displayName || firebaseUser.email!.split('@')[0],\n        role: UserRole.PATIENT,\n        photoURL: firebaseUser.photoURL || undefined,\n        emailVerified: firebaseUser.emailVerified,\n      };\n      try {\n        fallback.token = await firebaseUser.getIdToken(false);\n      } catch {\n        // Ignore logout errors\n      }\n      return fallback;\n    }\n  }\n\n  /**\n   * Maneja errores de autenticación\n   */\n  private handleAuthError(error: any): Error {\n    const errorMessages: Record<string, string> = {\n      'auth/email-already-in-use': 'Este email ya está registrado',\n      'auth/invalid-email': 'Email inválido',\n      'auth/operation-not-allowed': 'Operación no permitida',\n      'auth/weak-password': 'La contraseña es muy débil',\n      'auth/user-disabled': 'Usuario deshabilitado',\n      'auth/user-not-found': 'Usuario no encontrado',\n      'auth/wrong-password': 'Contraseña incorrecta',\n      'auth/invalid-credential': 'Credenciales inválidas',\n      'auth/popup-closed-by-user': 'Ventana cerrada por el usuario',\n      'auth/cancelled-popup-request': 'Solicitud cancelada',\n      'auth/popup-blocked': 'Ventana emergente bloqueada',\n      'auth/too-many-requests': 'Demasiados intentos. Intenta más tarde',\n      'auth/network-request-failed': 'Error de conexión',\n    };\n\n    const message = errorMessages[error.code] || error.message || 'Error de autenticación';\n\n    return new Error(message);\n  }\n}\n\n// Instancia singleton\nlet authServiceInstance: AuthService | null = null;\n\n/**\n * Obtiene la instancia del servicio de autenticación\n */\nexport const getAuthService = (): AuthService => {\n  if (!authServiceInstance) {\n    authServiceInstance = new AuthService();\n  }\n  return authServiceInstance;\n};\n\n// Exportación por defecto\nexport default AuthService;\n","/**\n * Hook useAuth unificado para toda la plataforma AltaMedica\n * Migrado desde auth-service y mejorado\n */\n\n'use client';\n\n// Import Next.js router safely for client-side usage\nimport { useRouter as useNextRouter } from 'next/navigation';\n// Import UserRole from types package\nimport { UserRole } from '@altamedica/types';\nimport { ReactNode, createContext, useCallback, useContext, useEffect, useState } from 'react';\nimport {\n  AuthState,\n  LoginCredentials,\n  RegisterData,\n  User,\n  getAuthService,\n} from '../services/AuthService';\n\n// Simple logger implementation to avoid circular dependencies\ntype LogData = unknown;\nconst logger = {\n  info: (message: string, data?: LogData) => {\n    if (typeof console !== 'undefined' && process.env.NODE_ENV !== 'production') {\n      console.log(message, data);\n    }\n  },\n  warn: (message: string, data?: LogData) => {\n    if (typeof console !== 'undefined') {\n      console.warn(message, data);\n    }\n  },\n  error: (message: string, data?: LogData) => {\n    if (typeof console !== 'undefined') {\n      console.error(message, data);\n    }\n  },\n  debug: (message: string, data?: LogData) => {\n    if (typeof console !== 'undefined' && process.env.NODE_ENV !== 'production') {\n      console.debug(message, data);\n    }\n  },\n};\n// Rutas por rol - Redirecciones corregidas por aplicación\nconst ROLE_ROUTES: Record<UserRole, string> = {\n  [UserRole.ADMIN]: 'http://localhost:3005', // Admin app (puerto 3005)\n  [UserRole.DOCTOR]: 'http://localhost:3002', // Doctors app (puerto 3002)\n  [UserRole.PATIENT]: 'http://localhost:3003', // Patients app (puerto 3003)\n  [UserRole.COMPANY]: 'http://localhost:3004', // Companies app (puerto 3004)\n};\n\n// Ruta por defecto para roles desconocidos o undefined\nconst DEFAULT_ROUTE = 'http://localhost:3000';\n\n/**\n * Obtiene la ruta apropiada para un rol dado, con redirección a aplicación específica\n */\nconst getRoleRoute = (role: string | UserRole | undefined): string => {\n  if (!role) {\n    logger.warn(`[AuthProvider] Sin rol definido. Redirigiendo a web-app por defecto.`, null);\n    return DEFAULT_ROUTE;\n  }\n\n  // Intentar encontrar la ruta exacta primero\n  if (ROLE_ROUTES[role as UserRole]) {\n    const route = ROLE_ROUTES[role as UserRole];\n    logger.info(`[AuthProvider] Redirigiendo ${role} a: ${route}`, { role, route });\n    return route;\n  }\n\n  // Mapeo de roles legacy que pueden existir por inconsistencias previas\n  const legacyRoleMappings: Record<string, string> = {\n    'company-admin': 'http://localhost:3004', // Mapear a companies app\n    company_admin: 'http://localhost:3004',\n    nurse: 'http://localhost:3002', // Los nurses van a doctors app\n    staff: 'http://localhost:3002', // Staff médico va a doctors app\n  };\n\n  if (legacyRoleMappings[role.toLowerCase()]) {\n    const route = legacyRoleMappings[role.toLowerCase()];\n    logger.warn(`[AuthProvider] Mapeando rol legacy \"${role}\" a: ${route}`, { role, route });\n    return route;\n  }\n\n  logger.warn(`[AuthProvider] Rol desconocido: \"${role}\". Redirigiendo a web-app por defecto.`, {\n    role,\n  });\n  return DEFAULT_ROUTE;\n};\n\n// Contexto de autenticación\ninterface AuthContextValue extends AuthState {\n  // Métodos de autenticación\n  login: (credentials: LoginCredentials) => Promise<void>;\n  loginWithGoogle: () => Promise<void>;\n  signUp: (data: RegisterData) => Promise<void>; // Renombrado de register a signUp\n  logout: () => Promise<void>;\n  resetPassword: (email: string) => Promise<void>;\n  updateProfile: (updates: Partial<User>) => Promise<void>;\n\n  // Helpers\n  hasRole: (role: UserRole) => boolean;\n  hasAnyRole: (roles: UserRole[]) => boolean;\n  isDoctor: () => boolean;\n  isPatient: () => boolean;\n  isAdmin: () => boolean;\n  isCompanyUser: () => boolean;\n  canAccessTelemedicine: () => boolean;\n  hasCompletedProfile: () => boolean;\n  checkSession: () => Promise<boolean>;\n\n  // Métodos de navegación\n  redirectToRole: () => void;\n  redirectToLogin: () => void;\n}\n\nconst AuthContext = createContext<AuthContextValue | undefined>(undefined);\n\n// Provider de autenticación\nexport interface AuthProviderProps {\n  children: ReactNode;\n  redirectOnLogin?: boolean;\n  redirectOnLogout?: boolean;\n  loginPath?: string;\n  protectedPaths?: string[];\n}\n\nexport function AuthProvider({\n  children,\n  redirectOnLogin = true,\n  redirectOnLogout = true,\n  loginPath = '/login',\n  protectedPaths = [],\n}: AuthProviderProps) {\n  const router = useNextRouter();\n  const authService = getAuthService();\n\n  const [authState, setAuthState] = useState<AuthState>({\n    user: null,\n    isAuthenticated: false,\n    isLoading: true,\n    error: null,\n  });\n\n  // Cargar usuario inicial\n  useEffect(() => {\n    const loadUser = async () => {\n      try {\n        const user = await authService.getCurrentUser();\n        setAuthState({\n          user,\n          isAuthenticated: !!user,\n          isLoading: false,\n          error: null,\n        });\n      } catch (error) {\n        setAuthState({\n          user: null,\n          isAuthenticated: false,\n          isLoading: false,\n          error: 'Error loading user',\n        });\n      }\n    };\n\n    loadUser();\n\n    // Suscribirse a cambios de autenticación\n    const unsubscribe = authService.onAuthStateChange((user) => {\n      setAuthState({\n        user,\n        isAuthenticated: !!user,\n        isLoading: false,\n        error: null,\n      });\n    });\n\n    return unsubscribe;\n  }, [authService]);\n\n  // Proteger rutas\n  useEffect(() => {\n    if (!authState.isLoading && protectedPaths.length > 0) {\n      const currentPath = window.location.pathname;\n      const isProtected = protectedPaths.some((path) => currentPath.startsWith(path));\n\n      if (isProtected && !authState.isAuthenticated) {\n        const path = loginPath || '/login';\n        router?.push(path);\n      }\n    }\n  }, [authState.isLoading, authState.isAuthenticated, protectedPaths, loginPath, router]);\n\n  // Métodos de autenticación\n  const login = useCallback(\n    async (credentials: LoginCredentials) => {\n      setAuthState((prev) => ({ ...prev, isLoading: true, error: null }));\n\n      try {\n        const user = await authService.login(credentials);\n\n        setAuthState({\n          user,\n          isAuthenticated: true,\n          isLoading: false,\n          error: null,\n        });\n\n        if (redirectOnLogin && user.role) {\n          const route = getRoleRoute(user.role);\n          // Si es una URL externa (diferente aplicación), usar window.location\n          if (route.startsWith('http')) {\n            window.location.href = route;\n          } else {\n            router?.push(route);\n          }\n        }\n      } catch (error: any) {\n        setAuthState({\n          user: null,\n          isAuthenticated: false,\n          isLoading: false,\n          error: error.message,\n        });\n        throw error;\n      }\n    },\n    [authService, redirectOnLogin, router],\n  );\n\n  const loginWithGoogle = useCallback(async () => {\n    setAuthState((prev) => ({ ...prev, isLoading: true, error: null }));\n\n    try {\n      const user = await authService.loginWithGoogle();\n\n      setAuthState({\n        user,\n        isAuthenticated: true,\n        isLoading: false,\n        error: null,\n      });\n\n      if (redirectOnLogin && user.role) {\n        const route = getRoleRoute(user.role);\n        // Si es una URL externa (diferente aplicación), usar window.location\n        if (route.startsWith('http')) {\n          window.location.href = route;\n        } else {\n          router?.push(route);\n        }\n      }\n    } catch (error: any) {\n      setAuthState({\n        user: null,\n        isAuthenticated: false,\n        isLoading: false,\n        error: error.message,\n      });\n      throw error;\n    }\n  }, [authService, redirectOnLogin, router]);\n\n  const signUp = useCallback(\n    async (data: RegisterData) => {\n      // Renombrado de register a signUp\n      setAuthState((prev) => ({ ...prev, isLoading: true, error: null }));\n\n      try {\n        const user = await authService.signUp(data); // Llamar a signUp en el servicio\n\n        setAuthState({\n          user,\n          isAuthenticated: true,\n          isLoading: false,\n          error: null,\n        });\n\n        if (redirectOnLogin && user.role) {\n          const route = getRoleRoute(user.role);\n          // Si es una URL externa (diferente aplicación), usar window.location\n          if (route.startsWith('http')) {\n            window.location.href = route;\n          } else {\n            router?.push(route);\n          }\n        }\n      } catch (error: any) {\n        setAuthState({\n          user: null,\n          isAuthenticated: false,\n          isLoading: false,\n          error: error.message,\n        });\n        throw error;\n      }\n    },\n    [authService, redirectOnLogin, router],\n  );\n\n  const logout = useCallback(async () => {\n    setAuthState((prev) => ({ ...prev, isLoading: true }));\n\n    try {\n      await authService.logout();\n\n      setAuthState({\n        user: null,\n        isAuthenticated: false,\n        isLoading: false,\n        error: null,\n      });\n\n      if (redirectOnLogout) {\n        router?.push('/');\n      }\n    } catch (error: any) {\n      setAuthState((prev) => ({\n        ...prev,\n        isLoading: false,\n        error: error.message,\n      }));\n      throw error;\n    }\n  }, [authService, redirectOnLogout, router]);\n\n  const resetPassword = useCallback(\n    async (email: string) => {\n      await authService.resetPassword(email);\n    },\n    [authService],\n  );\n\n  const updateProfile = useCallback(\n    async (updates: Partial<User>) => {\n      if (!authState.user) {\n        throw new Error('No user logged in');\n      }\n\n      setAuthState((prev) => ({ ...prev, isLoading: true }));\n\n      try {\n        await authService.updateUserProfile(authState.user.id, updates);\n\n        setAuthState((prev) => ({\n          ...prev,\n          user: prev.user ? { ...prev.user, ...updates } : null,\n          isLoading: false,\n        }));\n      } catch (error: any) {\n        setAuthState((prev) => ({\n          ...prev,\n          isLoading: false,\n          error: error.message,\n        }));\n        throw error;\n      }\n    },\n    [authService, authState.user],\n  );\n\n  // Helpers\n  const hasRole = useCallback(\n    (role: UserRole): boolean => {\n      return authState.user?.role === role;\n    },\n    [authState.user],\n  );\n\n  const hasAnyRole = useCallback(\n    (roles: UserRole[]): boolean => {\n      return !!authState.user && roles.includes(authState.user.role);\n    },\n    [authState.user],\n  );\n\n  const isDoctor = useCallback(() => hasRole(UserRole.DOCTOR), [hasRole]);\n  const isPatient = useCallback(() => hasRole(UserRole.PATIENT), [hasRole]);\n  const isAdmin = useCallback(() => hasRole(UserRole.ADMIN), [hasRole]);\n  const isCompanyUser = useCallback(() => {\n    return hasRole(UserRole.COMPANY); // Simplificado a solo COMPANY\n  }, [hasRole]);\n\n  const canAccessTelemedicine = useCallback(() => {\n    return (\n      authState.isAuthenticated &&\n      authState.user?.profileComplete === true &&\n      authState.user?.emailVerified === true\n    );\n  }, [authState]);\n\n  const hasCompletedProfile = useCallback(() => {\n    return authState.user?.profileComplete === true;\n  }, [authState.user]);\n\n  // Verificar sesión SSO\n  const checkSession = useCallback(async (): Promise<boolean> => {\n    try {\n      // Verificar si hay usuario en el estado actual\n      if (authState.user && authState.isAuthenticated) {\n        return true;\n      }\n\n      // Intentar obtener el usuario actual del servicio\n      const user = await authService.getCurrentUser();\n\n      if (user) {\n        setAuthState({\n          user,\n          isAuthenticated: true,\n          isLoading: false,\n          error: null,\n        });\n        return true;\n      }\n\n      return false;\n    } catch (error) {\n      logger.error('[useAuth] Error verificando sesión:', error);\n      return false;\n    }\n  }, [authState, authService]);\n\n  // Navegación\n  const redirectToRole = useCallback(() => {\n    if (authState.user?.role) {\n      const route = getRoleRoute(authState.user.role);\n      // Si es una URL externa (diferente aplicación), usar window.location\n      if (route.startsWith('http')) {\n        window.location.href = route;\n      } else {\n        router?.push(route);\n      }\n    }\n  }, [authState.user, router]);\n\n  const redirectToLogin = useCallback(() => {\n    const path = loginPath || '/login';\n    router?.push(path);\n  }, [router, loginPath]);\n\n  const value: AuthContextValue = {\n    ...authState,\n    login,\n    loginWithGoogle,\n    signUp, // Exponer signUp en el contexto\n    logout,\n    resetPassword,\n    updateProfile,\n    hasRole,\n    hasAnyRole,\n    isDoctor,\n    isPatient,\n    isAdmin,\n    isCompanyUser,\n    canAccessTelemedicine,\n    hasCompletedProfile,\n    checkSession,\n    redirectToRole,\n    redirectToLogin,\n  };\n\n  return <AuthContext.Provider value={value}>{children}</AuthContext.Provider>;\n}\n\n// Hook principal\nexport function useAuth(): AuthContextValue {\n  const context = useContext(AuthContext);\n\n  if (!context) {\n    throw new Error('useAuth must be used within AuthProvider');\n  }\n\n  return context;\n}\n\n// Hook para proteger rutas\nexport function useProtectedRoute(allowedRoles?: UserRole[]) {\n  const { isAuthenticated, isLoading, user, redirectToLogin } = useAuth();\n  const router = useNextRouter();\n\n  useEffect(() => {\n    if (!isLoading) {\n      if (!isAuthenticated) {\n        redirectToLogin();\n      } else if (allowedRoles && user && !allowedRoles.includes(user.role)) {\n        router?.push('/unauthorized');\n      }\n    }\n  }, [isAuthenticated, isLoading, user, allowedRoles, redirectToLogin, router]);\n\n  return {\n    isAuthenticated,\n    isLoading,\n    hasAccess: !allowedRoles || (user && allowedRoles.includes(user.role)),\n  };\n}\n\n// Hook para requerir autenticación\nexport function useRequireAuth() {\n  const { isAuthenticated, isLoading, redirectToLogin } = useAuth();\n\n  useEffect(() => {\n    if (!isLoading && !isAuthenticated) {\n      redirectToLogin();\n    }\n  }, [isAuthenticated, isLoading, redirectToLogin]);\n\n  return { isAuthenticated, isLoading };\n}\n\n// Hook para roles específicos\nexport function useRole(requiredRole: any): any {\n  const { user, hasRole } = useAuth();\n\n  return {\n    hasRequiredRole: hasRole(requiredRole),\n    currentRole: user?.role || null,\n  };\n}\n\n// Exportar todo\nexport { AuthContext };\nexport type { AuthState, LoginCredentials, RegisterData, User };\n\n","'use client';\n// @altamedica/auth/client - Exports }\n}\n\nexport interface AutoRedirectConfig {\n  cookieNames?: string[]; // nombres posibles del token (ej: auth-token, altamedica_token)\n  enforceRole?: UserRole; // si la app es específica de rol, Usuario con rol distinto accede a app equivocada\n  if (cfg.redirectIfMismatch && role && role !== appRole) {\n    if (cfg.mismatchStrategy === 'home-gateway') {\n      const gateway = cfg.gatewayUrl } from 'next/server';\nimport { AUTH_COOKIES, LEGACY_AUTH_COOKIES } from '../constants/cookies';\n\n// Simple logger implementation to avoid circular dependencies\nconst logger = {\n  info: (message: string, data?: any) => {\n    if (typeof console !== 'undefined' && process.env.NODE_ENV !== 'production') {\n      console.log(message, data);\n    }\n  },\n  warn: (message: string, data?: any) => console.error(message, data);\n    }\n  },\n  debug: (message: string, data?: any) => {\n    if (typeof console !== 'undefined' && process.env.NODE_ENV !== 'production') {\n      console.debug(message, data);\n    }\n  },\n};\ninterface AuthConfig {\n  loginUrl?: string;\n  apiUrl?: string;\n  allowedRoles?: string[];\n}\n\nconst DEFAULT_CONFIG: AuthConfig = {\n  loginUrl: 'http://localhost:3000/login',\n  apiUrl: 'http://localhost:3008/api/v1/auth/verify',\n};\n\nexport async function authGuard(\n  request: NextRequest,\n  config: AuthConfig = {},\n): Promise<NextResponse | null> {\n  const { loginUrl, apiUrl, allowedRoles } = { ...DEFAULT_CONFIG, ...config };\n\n  try {\n    // 1. Obtener cookies de la request (nuevo estándar + fallback legacy)\n    const authToken =\n      request.cookies.get(AUTH_COOKIES.token) || request.cookies.get(LEGACY_AUTH_COOKIES.token);\n    const refreshToken =\n      request.cookies.get(AUTH_COOKIES.refresh) || request.cookies.get(LEGACY_AUTH_COOKIES.refresh);\n\n    // 2. Si no hay cookies, redirigir a login\n    if (!authToken && !refreshToken) {\n      logger.info('[AuthGuard] No auth cookies found, redirecting to login');\n      return NextResponse.redirect(new URL(loginUrl!));\n    }\n\n    // 3. Verificar token con el API server\n    const verifyResponse = await fetch(apiUrl!, {\n      method: 'GET',\n      headers: {\n        Cookie: request.headers.get('cookie') || '',\n        'Content-Type': 'application/json',\n      },\n      credentials: 'include',\n    });\n\n    // 4. Si el token es inválido, redirigir a login\n    if (!verifyResponse.ok) {\n      logger.info('[AuthGuard] Token verification failed, redirecting to login');\n      return NextResponse.redirect(new URL(loginUrl!));\n    }\n\n    const { user } = await verifyResponse.json();\n\n    // 5. Verificar rol si es necesario\n    if (allowedRoles && allowedRoles.length > 0) {\n      if (!allowedRoles.includes(user.role)) {\n        logger.info(\n          `[AuthGuard] User role ${user.role} not allowed, need one of: ${allowedRoles.join(', ')}`,\n        );\n        return NextResponse.redirect(new URL('/unauthorized', request.url));\n      }\n    }\n\n    // 6. Agregar información del usuario a los headers\n    const response = NextResponse.next();\n    response.headers.set('X-User-Id', user.uid);\n    response.headers.set('X-User-Role', user.role);\n    response.headers.set('X-User-Email', user.email || '');\n\n    // 7. Si hay una nueva cookie de auth (renovación), pasarla\n    const setCookieHeader = verifyResponse.headers.get('set-cookie');\n    if (setCookieHeader) {\n      response.headers.set('set-cookie', setCookieHeader);\n    }\n\n    return null; // Permitir acceso\n  } catch (error) {\n    logger.error('[AuthGuard] Error:', error);\n    // En caso de error, redirigir a login por seguridad\n    return NextResponse.redirect(new URL(loginUrl!));\n  }\n}\n\n/**\n * Middleware para Next.js\n * Usar en middleware.ts de cada aplicación\n */\nexport function createAuthMiddleware(config: AuthConfig = {}) {\n  return async function middleware(request: NextRequest) {\n    // Rutas que NO requieren autenticación\n    const publicPaths = [\n      '/login',\n      '/register',\n      '/forgot-password',\n      '/api/health',\n      '/_next',\n      '/favicon.ico',\n      '/public',\n    ];\n\n    // Verificar si es una ruta pública\n    const isPublicPath = publicPaths.some((path) => request.nextUrl.pathname.startsWith(path));\n\n    if (isPublicPath) {\n      return NextResponse.next();\n    }\n\n    // Aplicar auth guard\n    const authResponse = await authGuard(request, config);\n\n    // Si authGuard retorna una respuesta (redirect), usarla\n    if (authResponse) {\n      return authResponse;\n    }\n\n    // Si no hay respuesta, permitir acceso\n    return NextResponse.next();\n  };\n}\n","import { createCipheriv, createDecipheriv, createHmac, randomBytes, timingSafeEqual } from 'crypto';\nimport { authenticator } from 'otplib';\n\n/**\n * Utilidades MFA (TOTP) - GAP-002-T1\n * - Generación de secreto base32\n * - Hash irreversible (HMAC-SHA256 + pepper)\n * - Cifrado reversible opcional (AES-256-GCM)\n * - Verificación TOTP con ventana corta\n */\n\nexport interface GenerateSecretOptions {\n  /** Nombre de la cuenta (email del usuario) para etiqueta en app Authenticator */\n  accountName: string;\n  /** Nombre de la entidad/issuer mostrado en la app */\n  issuer?: string;\n  /** Pepper global (NO almacenar en BD) */\n  pepper: string;\n  /** Clave AES-256 para cifrado reversible (32 bytes base64 o hex) */\n  encryptionKey?: Buffer | string;\n}\n\nexport interface GeneratedMfaSecret {\n  secret: string; // base32\n  otpauthUrl: string;\n  secretHash: string; // HMAC hash irreversible\n  secretEnc?: string; // Cifrado reversible base64 (iv:ciphertext:tag)\n}\n\n// Normaliza key AES desde base64/hex a Buffer 32 bytes\nfunction normalizeAesKey(key: string | Buffer): Buffer {\n  if (Buffer.isBuffer(key)) return key;\n  if (key.length === 44 && key.endsWith('=')) return Buffer.from(key, 'base64');\n  if (key.length === 64) return Buffer.from(key, 'hex');\n  throw new Error('encryptionKey debe ser buffer o base64(32 bytes) o hex(32 bytes)');\n}\n\nexport function generateMfaSecret(opts: GenerateSecretOptions): GeneratedMfaSecret {\n  const { accountName, issuer = 'AltaMedica', pepper, encryptionKey } = opts;\n  const secret = authenticator.generateSecret();\n  const otpauthUrl = authenticator.keyuri(accountName, issuer, secret);\n  const secretHash = hashSecret(secret, pepper);\n  let secretEnc: string | undefined;\n  if (encryptionKey) {\n    secretEnc = encryptSecret(secret, encryptionKey);\n  }\n  return { secret, otpauthUrl, secretHash, secretEnc };\n}\n\nexport function hashSecret(secret: string, pepper: string): string {\n  return createHmac('sha256', pepper).update(secret).digest('hex');\n}\n\nexport function encryptSecret(secret: string, key: string | Buffer): string {\n  const k = normalizeAesKey(key);\n  const iv = randomBytes(12); // GCM 96 bits\n  const cipher = createCipheriv('aes-256-gcm', k, iv);\n  const ct = Buffer.concat([cipher.update(secret, 'utf8'), cipher.final()]);\n  const tag = cipher.getAuthTag();\n  return `${iv.toString('base64')}:${ct.toString('base64')}:${tag.toString('base64')}`;\n}\n\nexport function decryptSecret(enc: string, key: string | Buffer): string {\n  const k = normalizeAesKey(key);\n  const [ivB64, ctB64, tagB64] = enc.split(':');\n  if (!ivB64 || !ctB64 || !tagB64) throw new Error('Formato cifrado inválido');\n  const iv = Buffer.from(ivB64, 'base64');\n  const ct = Buffer.from(ctB64, 'base64');\n  const tag = Buffer.from(tagB64, 'base64');\n  const decipher = createDecipheriv('aes-256-gcm', k, iv);\n  decipher.setAuthTag(tag);\n  const pt = Buffer.concat([decipher.update(ct), decipher.final()]);\n  return pt.toString('utf8');\n}\n\nexport interface VerifyTotpOptions {\n  token: string;\n  // Usar secret en claro (si recién generado) o descifrado; NO almacenar en claro después.\n  secret: string;\n  window?: number; // ventana de tolerancia (default 1 = +-30s)\n}\n\nexport function verifyTotpCode({ token, secret, window = 1 }: VerifyTotpOptions): boolean {\n  if (!/^[0-9]{6}$/.test(token)) return false;\n  if (window === 1) {\n    return authenticator.verify({ token, secret });\n  }\n  // Ajuste temporal de la ventana usando options (no tipado), luego se restaura\n  const opts: any = authenticator.options || {};\n  const originalWindow = opts.window;\n  try {\n    opts.window = window;\n    authenticator.options = opts;\n    return authenticator.verify({ token, secret });\n  } finally {\n    opts.window = originalWindow;\n    authenticator.options = opts;\n  }\n}\n\nexport function constantTimeHashCompare(a: string, b: string): boolean {\n  const aBuf = Buffer.from(a, 'utf8');\n  const bBuf = Buffer.from(b, 'utf8');\n  if (aBuf.length !== bBuf.length)
